strators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: 20th century births, British or Irish individuals, Half-bloods,     and 5 more    Hopkins family   Hufflepuffs   Hufflepuffs Sorted in 1991   Males   Wizards             English     Deutsch   Español   Français   Polski   Русский               Wayne Hopkins              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                   Wayne Hopkins   Biographical information  Born Between 1 September 1979 and 31 August 1980   Blood status Half-blood[1]   Nationality British or Irish[2]    Physical information  Species Human[3]   Gender Male[3]    Relationship information  Family members Carl Hopkins (possible relative)    Affiliation  House Hufflepuff[3]   Loyalty Hopkins family[3]Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry[3]Hufflepuff[3]   [Source]  Wayne Hopkins was a half-blood wizard who began attending Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry in 1991. He was in the same year as Harry Potter and was sorted into the Hufflepuff house.[3]  Etymology The name "Wayne" is from an occupational surname meaning "wagon maker", derived from Old English wægn "wagon".  Appearances Harry Potter and Me (First mentioned) Pottermore (Mentioned only) Wizarding World (Mentioned only) Notes and references   ↑ Harry Potter and Me  ↑ "World Exclusive Interview with J K Rowling," South West News Service, 8 July 2000  - "Hogwarts just serves Britain and Ireland."  ↑ 3.0 3.1 3.2 3.3 3.4 3.5 3.6 Writing by J. K. Rowling: "The Original Forty" at Wizarding World              Categories         Categories:   20th century births    British or Irish individuals    Half-bloods    Hopkins family    Hufflepuffs    Hufflepuffs Sorted in 1991    Males    Wizards             Languages      Deutsch Español Français Polski Русский      *Disclosure: Some of the links above are affiliate links, meaning, at no additional cost to you, Fandom will earn a commission if you click thro